[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":2041},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F04\u002F13\u002Fmonorepo-vite-pnpm-vue3-setup\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F04\u002F13\u002Fmonorepo-vite-pnpm-vue3-setup\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F04\u002F13\u002Fmonorepo-vite-pnpm-vue3-setup\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F04\u002F13\u002Fmonorepo-vite-pnpm-vue3-setup\u002F":2017,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2024\u002F04\u002F13\u002Fmonorepo-vite-pnpm-vue3-setup\u002F":2026},"\u002Fother\u002F20240413\u002F3177435894\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":2000,"date":2001,"description":2002,"extension":97,"lang":2003,"meta":2004,"navigation":1916,"path":2005,"readingMinutes":2006,"seo":2007,"standalone":2008,"stem":2009,"tags":2010,"tldr":2013,"updated":2014,"url":2015,"__hash__":2016},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fmonorepo-vite-pnpm-vue3-setup.md","Monorepo? Another Way to Manage Projects — Building a Vue3 Monorepo With Vite + pnpm","8943571316",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1988},"minimark",[11,20,25,28,32,44,47,52,55,76,83,89,92,236,239,242,256,259,265,272,275,278,281,567,570,573,579,583,594,597,602,605,608,613,616,619,624,627,630,648,651,655,658,691,706,717,720,724,727,766,773,784,790,814,820,841,847,853,856,862,877,1035,1058,1065,1197,1210,1213,1228,1247,1251,1254,1464,1481,1612,1629,1632,1644,1650,1656,1674,1690,1694,1697,1714,1717,1730,1733,1739,1758,1824,1836,1839,1860,1863,1958,1961,1964,1973,1984],[12,13,16],"callout",{"title":14,"type":15},"Note","note",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Monorepo = \"Mono\" (single) + \"Repo\" (Repository) — multiple projects in one Git repo. It's the opposite of the \"one project, one repo\" Monolith pattern. In JavaScript, the most common way to build one is pnpm workspace paired with Vite.",[21,22,24],"h2",{"id":23},"intro","Intro",[17,26,27],{},"What is a Monorepo? How does it differ from a regular project layout? I had a need for one recently, so I'm writing this up.",[21,29,31],{"id":30},"what-is-a-monorepo","What is a Monorepo?",[17,33,34,35,39,40,43],{},"Monorepo — what's that? It's two words mashed together: ",[36,37,38],"strong",{},"Mono"," (meaning \"single\") + ",[36,41,42],{},"Repo"," (short for Repository). So Monorepo literally means \"single repository\".",[17,45,46],{},"Sounds a bit abstract? No worries. Let's talk about other project layouts first, then come back to Monorepo.",[48,49,51],"h3",{"id":50},"monolith-repository","Monolith Repository",[17,53,54],{},"When you build a project, you typically go through these steps:",[56,57,58,62,70,73],"ul",{},[59,60,61],"li",{},"Create the project",[59,63,64,65,69],{},"Initialize version control (",[66,67,68],"code",{},"git init",")",[59,71,72],{},"Build the features",[59,74,75],{},"Push to a remote (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, etc.)",[17,77,78],{},[79,80],"img",{"alt":81,"src":82},"Repository","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-04-13%2023.50.43.png",[17,84,85,86,88],{},"The project gets its own Git repo. That's the most basic project layout, and it's called a ",[36,87,51],{}," (or just \"Monolith\") — a single-project Repository.",[17,90,91],{},"The Monolith layout looks something like this:",[93,94,99],"pre",{"className":95,"code":96,"language":97,"meta":98,"style":98},"language-md shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","- Repository\n  - .git\n  - README.md\n  - package.json\n  - src\n    - components\n      - Button\n      - Input\n      - ...\n    - pages\n      - index\n      - shopping\n      - admin\n      - ...\n  - public\n  - ...other files\n","md","",[66,100,101,114,123,131,139,147,156,165,173,181,189,197,205,213,220,228],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,103,106,110],"span",{"class":104,"line":105},"line",1,[102,107,109],{"class":108},"syBk-","-",[102,111,113],{"class":112},"s8XSl"," Repository\n",[102,115,117,120],{"class":104,"line":116},2,[102,118,119],{"class":108},"  -",[102,121,122],{"class":112}," .git\n",[102,124,126,128],{"class":104,"line":125},3,[102,127,119],{"class":108},[102,129,130],{"class":112}," README.md\n",[102,132,134,136],{"class":104,"line":133},4,[102,135,119],{"class":108},[102,137,138],{"class":112}," package.json\n",[102,140,142,144],{"class":104,"line":141},5,[102,143,119],{"class":108},[102,145,146],{"class":112}," src\n",[102,148,150,153],{"class":104,"line":149},6,[102,151,152],{"class":108},"    -",[102,154,155],{"class":112}," components\n",[102,157,159,162],{"class":104,"line":158},7,[102,160,161],{"class":108},"      -",[102,163,164],{"class":112}," Button\n",[102,166,168,170],{"class":104,"line":167},8,[102,169,161],{"class":108},[102,171,172],{"class":112}," Input\n",[102,174,176,178],{"class":104,"line":175},9,[102,177,161],{"class":108},[102,179,180],{"class":112}," ...\n",[102,182,184,186],{"class":104,"line":183},10,[102,185,152],{"class":108},[102,187,188],{"class":112}," pages\n",[102,190,192,194],{"class":104,"line":191},11,[102,193,161],{"class":108},[102,195,196],{"class":112}," index\n",[102,198,200,202],{"class":104,"line":199},12,[102,201,161],{"class":108},[102,203,204],{"class":112}," shopping\n",[102,206,208,210],{"class":104,"line":207},13,[102,209,161],{"class":108},[102,211,212],{"class":112}," admin\n",[102,214,216,218],{"class":104,"line":215},14,[102,217,161],{"class":108},[102,219,180],{"class":112},[102,221,223,225],{"class":104,"line":222},15,[102,224,119],{"class":108},[102,226,227],{"class":112}," public\n",[102,229,231,233],{"class":104,"line":230},16,[102,232,119],{"class":108},[102,234,235],{"class":112}," ...other files\n",[17,237,238],{},"One Git repo manages the whole project.",[17,240,241],{},"The Monolith setup is convenient and simple — a great choice for MVPs. But it has problems too. As the project grows, it gets harder to maintain. Say the project has these feature modules:",[56,243,244,247,250,253],{},[59,245,246],{},"Frontend home",[59,248,249],{},"Frontend shopping page",[59,251,252],{},"Admin backend",[59,254,255],{},"...and so on",[17,257,258],{},"Development and deployment slow down as the project gets bigger. Even a small change requires a full build + test + deploy cycle, and one bug anywhere can take the whole thing down:",[17,260,261],{},[79,262],{"alt":263,"src":264},"Bye bye","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002Fim-leaving-leaving.gif",[17,266,267,268,271],{},"To solve this, we get the next layout: ",[36,269,270],{},"Multi Repository",".",[48,273,270],{"id":274},"multi-repository",[17,276,277],{},"What is Multi Repository (Multi for short)? Take the Monolith and split it into multiple repos — each project gets its own. That way each one can be developed and deployed independently, solving Monolith's main problem.",[17,279,280],{},"The layout becomes:",[93,282,284],{"className":95,"code":283,"language":97,"meta":98,"style":98},"- A Repository\n  - .git\n  - README.md\n  - package.json\n  - src\n    - components\n      - Button\n      - Input\n      - ...\n    - pages\n      - index\n      - ...\n  - public\n  - ...other files\n- B Repository\n  - .git\n  - README.md\n  - package.json\n  - src\n    - components\n      - Button\n      - Input\n      - ...\n    - pages\n      - shopping\n      - ...\n  - public\n  - ...other files\n- C Repository\n  - .git\n  - README.md\n  - package.json\n  - src\n    - components\n      - Button\n      - Input\n      - ...\n    - pages\n      - admin\n      - ...\n  - public\n  - ...other files\n",[66,285,286,293,299,305,311,317,323,329,335,341,347,353,359,365,371,378,384,391,398,405,412,419,426,433,440,447,454,461,468,476,483,490,497,504,511,518,525,532,539,546,553,560],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,287,288,290],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,289,109],{"class":108},[102,291,292],{"class":112}," A Repository\n",[102,294,295,297],{"class":104,"line":116},[102,296,119],{"class":108},[102,298,122],{"class":112},[102,300,301,303],{"class":104,"line":125},[102,302,119],{"class":108},[102,304,130],{"class":112},[102,306,307,309],{"class":104,"line":133},[102,308,119],{"class":108},[102,310,138],{"class":112},[102,312,313,315],{"class":104,"line":141},[102,314,119],{"class":108},[102,316,146],{"class":112},[102,318,319,321],{"class":104,"line":149},[102,320,152],{"class":108},[102,322,155],{"class":112},[102,324,325,327],{"class":104,"line":158},[102,326,161],{"class":108},[102,328,164],{"class":112},[102,330,331,333],{"class":104,"line":167},[102,332,161],{"class":108},[102,334,172],{"class":112},[102,336,337,339],{"class":104,"line":175},[102,338,161],{"class":108},[102,340,180],{"class":112},[102,342,343,345],{"class":104,"line":183},[102,344,152],{"class":108},[102,346,188],{"class":112},[102,348,349,351],{"class":104,"line":191},[102,350,161],{"class":108},[102,352,196],{"class":112},[102,354,355,357],{"class":104,"line":199},[102,356,161],{"class":108},[102,358,180],{"class":112},[102,360,361,363],{"class":104,"line":207},[102,362,119],{"class":108},[102,364,227],{"class":112},[102,366,367,369],{"class":104,"line":215},[102,368,119],{"class":108},[102,370,235],{"class":112},[102,372,373,375],{"class":104,"line":222},[102,374,109],{"class":108},[102,376,377],{"class":112}," B Repository\n",[102,379,380,382],{"class":104,"line":230},[102,381,119],{"class":108},[102,383,122],{"class":112},[102,385,387,389],{"class":104,"line":386},17,[102,388,119],{"class":108},[102,390,130],{"class":112},[102,392,394,396],{"class":104,"line":393},18,[102,395,119],{"class":108},[102,397,138],{"class":112},[102,399,401,403],{"class":104,"line":400},19,[102,402,119],{"class":108},[102,404,146],{"class":112},[102,406,408,410],{"class":104,"line":407},20,[102,409,152],{"class":108},[102,411,155],{"class":112},[102,413,415,417],{"class":104,"line":414},21,[102,416,161],{"class":108},[102,418,164],{"class":112},[102,420,422,424],{"class":104,"line":421},22,[102,423,161],{"class":108},[102,425,172],{"class":112},[102,427,429,431],{"class":104,"line":428},23,[102,430,161],{"class":108},[102,432,180],{"class":112},[102,434,436,438],{"class":104,"line":435},24,[102,437,152],{"class":108},[102,439,188],{"class":112},[102,441,443,445],{"class":104,"line":442},25,[102,444,161],{"class":108},[102,446,204],{"class":112},[102,448,450,452],{"class":104,"line":449},26,[102,451,161],{"class":108},[102,453,180],{"class":112},[102,455,457,459],{"class":104,"line":456},27,[102,458,119],{"class":108},[102,460,227],{"class":112},[102,462,464,466],{"class":104,"line":463},28,[102,465,119],{"class":108},[102,467,235],{"class":112},[102,469,471,473],{"class":104,"line":470},29,[102,472,109],{"class":108},[102,474,475],{"class":112}," C Repository\n",[102,477,479,481],{"class":104,"line":478},30,[102,480,119],{"class":108},[102,482,122],{"class":112},[102,484,486,488],{"class":104,"line":485},31,[102,487,119],{"class":108},[102,489,130],{"class":112},[102,491,493,495],{"class":104,"line":492},32,[102,494,119],{"class":108},[102,496,138],{"class":112},[102,498,500,502],{"class":104,"line":499},33,[102,501,119],{"class":108},[102,503,146],{"class":112},[102,505,507,509],{"class":104,"line":506},34,[102,508,152],{"class":108},[102,510,155],{"class":112},[102,512,514,516],{"class":104,"line":513},35,[102,515,161],{"class":108},[102,517,164],{"class":112},[102,519,521,523],{"class":104,"line":520},36,[102,522,161],{"class":108},[102,524,172],{"class":112},[102,526,528,530],{"class":104,"line":527},37,[102,529,161],{"class":108},[102,531,180],{"class":112},[102,533,535,537],{"class":104,"line":534},38,[102,536,152],{"class":108},[102,538,188],{"class":112},[102,540,542,544],{"class":104,"line":541},39,[102,543,161],{"class":108},[102,545,212],{"class":112},[102,547,549,551],{"class":104,"line":548},40,[102,550,161],{"class":108},[102,552,180],{"class":112},[102,554,556,558],{"class":104,"line":555},41,[102,557,119],{"class":108},[102,559,227],{"class":112},[102,561,563,565],{"class":104,"line":562},42,[102,564,119],{"class":108},[102,566,235],{"class":112},[17,568,569],{},"This looks great — no more \"one bug takes down everything\". Each feature module is its own project, each one can ship independently.",[17,571,572],{},"But new problems show up. Look at the example above: Button and Input components are duplicated in every repo. That's duplication of effort, and when one of them breaks, you've gotta fix it in every project. Maintenance gets painful. Not just shared components either — CI\u002FCD setup, dependency versions, all of that gets harder to keep in sync. QAQ...",[17,574,575],{},[79,576],{"alt":577,"src":578},"Crashed out","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002F202404140133.jpg",[48,580,582],{"id":581},"mono-repository","Mono Repository",[17,584,585,586,590,591,271],{},"To solve ",[587,588,589],"em",{},"that",", we get the layout this post is actually about: ",[36,592,593],{},"Monorepo",[17,595,596],{},"Things might be getting confusing, so let me draw it out. First, Monolith:",[17,598,599],{},[79,600],{"alt":51,"src":601},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002FMonolith%20Repository.png",[17,603,604],{},"One project, one Repository, lots of feature modules inside, with the \"everything breaks together\" problem.",[17,606,607],{},"Then Multi:",[17,609,610],{},[79,611],{"alt":270,"src":612},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002FMulti%20Repository.png",[17,614,615],{},"Monolith split into multiple repos, each one independent. Solves Monolith's problems, introduces duplication problems.",[17,617,618],{},"Finally, Monorepo:",[17,620,621],{},[79,622],{"alt":582,"src":623},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002FMono%20Repository.png",[17,625,626],{},"In Monorepo, all the projects sit inside the same Repository, managed by one Git. Solves Multi's duplication problem because shared resources can actually be shared — they all live in the same place.",[17,628,629],{},"Monorepo isn't a free lunch either. A few downsides:",[56,631,632,639,642,645],{},[59,633,634,635,638],{},"The repo gets big — ",[66,636,637],{},"git clone"," takes longer",[59,640,641],{},"Shared code needs careful planning, otherwise projects affect each other",[59,643,644],{},"All projects share one repo, so you can't have per-project access control",[59,646,647],{},"Git repo size grows fast",[17,649,650],{},"So every layout has trade-offs. When picking one, think about what your project actually needs.",[21,652,654],{"id":653},"building-a-monorepo-with-vite","Building a Monorepo with Vite",[17,656,657],{},"Now let me walk through building a Vue3 Monorepo with Vite + pnpm. First, set up the environment:",[93,659,663],{"className":660,"code":661,"language":662,"meta":98,"style":98},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","mkdir monorepo-example-pnpm-vue3\ncd monorepo-example-pnpm-vue3\npnpm init\n","bash",[66,664,665,675,683],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,666,667,671],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,668,670],{"class":669},"smYoP","mkdir",[102,672,674],{"class":673},"sWayO"," monorepo-example-pnpm-vue3\n",[102,676,677,681],{"class":104,"line":116},[102,678,680],{"class":679},"stw71","cd",[102,682,674],{"class":673},[102,684,685,688],{"class":104,"line":125},[102,686,687],{"class":669},"pnpm",[102,689,690],{"class":673}," init\n",[17,692,693,694,701,702,705],{},"Next, a special setting. The pnpm ",[695,696,700],"a",{"href":697,"rel":698},"https:\u002F\u002Fpnpm.io\u002Fworkspaces",[699],"nofollow","Workspace"," docs say a Monorepo needs a ",[66,703,704],{},"pnpm-workspace.yaml"," file in the root. So create one in this project.",[12,707,708],{"title":14,"type":15},[17,709,710,712,713,716],{},[66,711,704],{}," tells pnpm \"this project is a Monorepo\". Running ",[66,714,715],{},"pnpm install"," will install dependencies for all the sub-projects.",[17,718,719],{},"What goes in it? Let's look at the Monorepo layout again:",[17,721,722],{},[79,723],{"alt":582,"src":623},[17,725,726],{},"One Git manages multiple projects, so a typical Monorepo looks like:",[93,728,730],{"className":95,"code":729,"language":97,"meta":98,"style":98},"- Git\n  - pnpm-workspace.yaml\n  - package.json\n  - apps\n  - packages\n",[66,731,732,739,746,752,759],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,733,734,736],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,735,109],{"class":108},[102,737,738],{"class":112}," Git\n",[102,740,741,743],{"class":104,"line":116},[102,742,119],{"class":108},[102,744,745],{"class":112}," pnpm-workspace.yaml\n",[102,747,748,750],{"class":104,"line":125},[102,749,119],{"class":108},[102,751,138],{"class":112},[102,753,754,756],{"class":104,"line":133},[102,755,119],{"class":108},[102,757,758],{"class":112}," apps\n",[102,760,761,763],{"class":104,"line":141},[102,762,119],{"class":108},[102,764,765],{"class":112}," packages\n",[17,767,768,769,772],{},"The ",[66,770,771],{},"apps"," folder is where the sub-projects live. Create it in the root:",[93,774,776],{"className":660,"code":775,"language":662,"meta":98,"style":98},"mkdir apps\n",[66,777,778],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,779,780,782],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,781,670],{"class":669},[102,783,758],{"class":673},[17,785,786,787,789],{},"Then write this to ",[66,788,704],{},":",[93,791,795],{"className":792,"code":793,"language":794,"meta":98,"style":98},"language-yaml shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","packages:\n  - apps\u002F*\n","yaml",[66,796,797,806],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,798,799,803],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,800,802],{"class":801},"syv7_","packages",[102,804,805],{"class":112},":\n",[102,807,808,811],{"class":104,"line":116},[102,809,810],{"class":112},"  - ",[102,812,813],{"class":673},"apps\u002F*\n",[17,815,816,817,819],{},"That's the basic Monorepo environment ready. Now let's create a Vue3 project. Move into ",[66,818,771],{}," and run:",[93,821,823],{"className":660,"code":822,"language":662,"meta":98,"style":98},"cd apps\npnpm create vue@latest\n",[66,824,825,831],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,826,827,829],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,828,680],{"class":679},[102,830,758],{"class":673},[102,832,833,835,838],{"class":104,"line":116},[102,834,687],{"class":669},[102,836,837],{"class":673}," create",[102,839,840],{"class":673}," vue@latest\n",[17,842,843,844,789],{},"I'll create one called ",[66,845,846],{},"shopping",[17,848,849],{},[79,850],{"alt":851,"src":852},"Vue Create","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-04-15%2013.38.35.png",[17,854,855],{},"After creation, the project should look like:",[17,857,858],{},[79,859],{"alt":860,"src":861},"Project structure","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fmonorepo\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-04-15%2013.40.05.png",[17,863,864,865,868,869,872,873,876],{},"Open ",[66,866,867],{},"apps\u002Fshopping\u002Fpackage.json"," and change the ",[66,870,871],{},"name"," to ",[66,874,875],{},"@apps\u002Fshopping"," so pnpm knows this project belongs to the Monorepo:",[93,878,882],{"className":879,"code":880,"language":881,"meta":98,"style":98},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"name\": \"@apps\u002Fshopping\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"vite\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\n    \"serve\": \"vite preview\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"vue\": \"^3.2.29\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@vitejs\u002Fplugin-vue\": \"^1.9.2\",\n    \"vite\": \"^2.7.13\"\n  }\n}\n","json",[66,883,884,889,904,916,928,936,948,960,970,975,982,992,996,1003,1015,1025,1030],{"__ignoreMap":98},[102,885,886],{"class":104,"line":105},[102,887,888],{"class":112},"{\n",[102,890,891,895,898,901],{"class":104,"line":116},[102,892,894],{"cl